%U A098209 4444444444488888888888,444444444444888888888888,44444444444448888888888888,4444444444444488888888888888,444444444444444888888888888888
%N A098209 a(n) = A067275(n+1)^2 - 1.
%C A098209 Certain functions of near or generalized repdigits provide interesting digit patterns like e.g: a(9) = -1 + (666666667)^2 = 444444444888888888.
%H A098209 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (111,-1110,1000).
%F A098209 From _Elmo R. Oliveira_, Jul 09 2026: (Start)
%F A098209 G.f.: 24*x*(2 - 35*x)/((1 - x)*(1 - 10*x)*(1 - 100*x)).
%F A098209 E.g.f.: 4*exp(x)*(-2 + exp(9*x) + exp(99*x))/9.
%F A098209 a(n) = 111*a(n-1) - 1110*a(n-2) + 1000*a(n-3).
%F A098209 a(n) = (4/9)*(10^n*(1 + 10^n) - 2) = A002280(n)*A073555(n+1). (End)
%Y A098209 Cf. A002280, A067275, A073555, A096507.
